  "suggestion": "Efficiency breaks when exploration cost > foraging gain. Spread first, then optimize energy per organism.; Efficiency (0.465) is the primary drag on fitness—a 23% gap from beautyScore. Compounded by spatialComposition (0.3, worst component) and diversityOfForms (0.456), organisms cluster inefficiently and waste energy. Survival depends on reducing per-organism energy overhead while increasing spatial spread. Strategy: boost moveSpeed and explorationDrive to force organisms away from birth cluster (improves spatialComposition); increase energyConserve and harvestThreshold to stop frivolous trail-laying and movement; boost resourceAttraction so energy expenditure pays off in food acquisition. Three organisms died at age ~270; better exploration + conservation extends lifespan and improves diversity.",
